# Security Policy for Salty

## Scope

This security policy applies to:
- The Salty web application hosted at https://salty.esolia.pro
- The Salty API endpoints at https://salty.esolia.pro/api/*
- The Salty source code repository at https://github.com/esolia/salty.esolia.pro

## Reporting Security Vulnerabilities

We welcome responsible disclosure of security vulnerabilities. Please report them to:
- Email: admin@esolia.co.jp
- Subject: "Salty Security Vulnerability"

## What to Report

We are interested in:
- Cryptographic implementation flaws
- Authentication/authorization bypasses
- Input validation vulnerabilities
- Cross-site scripting (XSS)
- Information disclosure
- Any vulnerability that could compromise user data

## What NOT to Report

Please do not report:
- Denial of Service (DoS) attacks
- Social engineering attempts
- Physical security issues
- Vulnerabilities in third-party services

## Response Timeline

- Initial response: Within 48 hours
- Status update: Within 7 days
- Resolution target: Within 30 days for critical issues

## Recognition

We appreciate security researchers who help us maintain a secure application. With your permission, we will acknowledge your contribution in our release notes.

## Safe Harbor

We will not pursue legal action against researchers who:
- Act in good faith
- Do not access or modify user data
- Do not disrupt our services
- Provide adequate time for patching

Last updated: 2025-06-30